TITLE: AST Traversal and Modification
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to traverse and modify an AST by implementing a NodeVisitor that removes all function bodies. The example demonstrates using NodeTraverser and extending NodeVisitorAbstract to process AST nodes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/catchpoint/webpagetest/blob/master/vendor/nikic/php-parser/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use PhpParser\Node;
use PhpParser\Node\Stmt\Function_;
use PhpParser\NodeTraverser;
use PhpParser\NodeVisitorAbstract;

$traverser = new NodeTraverser();
$traverser->addVisitor(new class extends NodeVisitorAbstract {
    public function enterNode(Node $node) {
        if ($node instanceof Function_) {
            // Clean out the function body
            $node->stmts = [];
        }
    }
});

$ast = $traverser->traverse($ast);
echo $dumper->dump($ast) . "\n";
```

