TITLE: Conditional Escaping of Tainted Input in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to conditionally apply taint escaping using a boolean parameter. The @psalm-taint-escape annotation uses a conditional expression to determine whether to escape HTML taint based on the function argument.
SOURCE: https://github.com/catchpoint/webpagetest/blob/master/vendor/vimeo/psalm/docs/security_analysis/avoiding_false_positives.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
/**
 * @param string $str
 * @param bool $escape
 * @psalm-taint-escape ($escape is true ? 'html' : null)
 */
function processVar(string $str, bool $escape = true) : string {
    if ($escape) {
      $str = str_replace(['<', '>'], '', $str);
    }
    return $str;
}

echo processVar($_GET['text'], false); // detects tainted HTML
echo processVar($_GET['text'], true); // considered secure
```

