TITLE: Basic Dot Access Data Usage in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates basic usage of the Data class including setting, getting, appending values, and checking existence using dot notation. Shows handling of default values and missing paths.
SOURCE: https://github.com/catchpoint/webpagetest/blob/master/vendor/dflydev/dot-access-data/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Dflydev\DotAccessData\Data;

$data = new Data;

$data->set('a.b.c', 'C');
$data->set('a.b.d', 'D1');
$data->append('a.b.d', 'D2');
$data->set('a.b.e', ['E0', 'E1', 'E2']);

// C
$data->get('a.b.c');

// ['D1', 'D2']
$data->get('a.b.d');

// ['E0', 'E1', 'E2']
$data->get('a.b.e');

// true
$data->has('a.b.c');

// false
$data->has('a.b.d.j');


// 'some-default-value'
$data->get('some.path.that.does.not.exist', 'some-default-value');

// throws a MissingPathException because no default was given
$data->get('some.path.that.does.not.exist');
```

