TITLE: Example of Type Safety Issue When Extending Generic Classes
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how extending the Container class can lead to type safety issues when the child class calls getInstance() with an incompatible type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/catchpoint/webpagetest/blob/master/vendor/vimeo/psalm/docs/running_psalm/issues/UnsafeGenericInstantiation.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

/**
 * @template T
 * @psalm-consistent-constructor
 */
class Container {
    /**
     * @var T
     */
    public $t;

    /**
     * @param T $t
     */
    public function __construct($t) {
        $this->t = $t;
    }

    /**
     * @template U
     * @param U $u
     * @return static<U>
     */
    public function getInstance($u) : static
    {
        return new static($u);
    }
}

/**
 * @extends Container<string>
 */
class StringContainer extends Container {}

$c = StringContainer::getInstance(new stdClass());
// creates StringContainer<stdClass>, clearly invalid
```

