TITLE: True Polyfill Usage Example
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating the use of Sodium Compat as a true polyfill for PHP 5.3.0+ without PECL extension.
SOURCE: https://github.com/catchpoint/webpagetest/blob/master/vendor/paragonie/sodium_compat/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
require_once "/path/to/sodium_compat/autoload.php";

$alice_kp = \Sodium\crypto_sign_keypair();
$alice_sk = \Sodium\crypto_sign_secretkey($alice_kp);
$alice_pk = \Sodium\crypto_sign_publickey($alice_kp);

$message = 'This is a test message.';
$signature = \Sodium\crypto_sign_detached($message, $alice_sk);
if (\Sodium\crypto_sign_verify_detached($signature, $message, $alice_pk)) {
    echo 'OK', PHP_EOL;
} else {
    throw new Exception('Invalid signature');
}
```

