TITLE: Emitting ImpureStaticVariable Warning in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This PHP code snippet demonstrates the emission of an ImpureStaticVariable warning by using a static variable in a function marked as pure using the @psalm-pure annotation. The function `addCumulative` contains a static variable that accumulates the input parameter `left`. Because the function is marked pure, any stateful operations like static variables should be avoided to maintain purity. The input is an integer, and the output is the same integer value. There are no external dependencies, but proper understanding of static variables and purity is required.
SOURCE: https://github.com/catchpoint/webpagetest/blob/master/vendor/vimeo/psalm/docs/running_psalm/issues/ImpureStaticVariable.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
<?php

/** @psalm-pure */
function addCumulative(int $left) : int {
    /** @var int */
    static $i = 0;
    $i += $left;
    return $left;
}
```

