TITLE: Demonstrating Reference Constraint Conflict in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how using by-reference variables with different types in conditional branches creates type conflicts. The code demonstrates assigning an integer and string reference to the same variable in different branches, which causes issues with type inference.
SOURCE: https://github.com/catchpoint/webpagetest/blob/master/vendor/vimeo/psalm/docs/running_psalm/issues/ConflictingReferenceConstraint.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

 class A {
    /** @var int */
    private $foo;

    public function __construct(int &$foo) {
        $this->foo = &$foo;
    }
}

class B {
    /** @var string */
    private $bar;

    public function __construct(string &$bar) {
        $this->bar = &$bar;
    }
}

if (rand(0, 1)) {
    $v = 5;
    $c = (new A($v)); // $v is constrained to an int
} else {
    $v = "hello";
    $c = (new B($v)); // $v is constrained to a string
}

$v = 8;
```

