TITLE: Using @psalm-immutable for Taint Specialization in Classes in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Shows how the @psalm-immutable annotation can be used on classes to achieve taint specialization, since immutability is a form of purity enforcement in Psalm.
SOURCE: https://github.com/catchpoint/webpagetest/blob/master/vendor/vimeo/psalm/docs/security_analysis/avoiding_false_positives.md#2025-04-21_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

/**
 * @psalm-immutable
 */
class User {
    public string $name;

    public function __construct(string $name) {
        $this->name = $name;
    }
}

/**
 * @psalm-taint-specialize
 */
function echoUserName(User $user) {
    echo $user->name; // No error
}

$user1 = new User("Keith");
$user2 = new User($_GET["name"]);

echoUserName($user1);
```

