TITLE: Example of Taint Issues in Classes Without Specialization in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Shows a case where Psalm incorrectly flags untainted class properties as tainted because the class doesn't use taint specialization, even when used with specialized functions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/catchpoint/webpagetest/blob/master/vendor/vimeo/psalm/docs/security_analysis/avoiding_false_positives.md#2025-04-21_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

class User {
    public string $name;

    public function __construct(string $name) {
        $this->name = $name;
    }
}

/**
 * @psalm-taint-specialize
 */
function echoUserName(User $user) {
    echo $user->name; // Error, detected tainted input
}

$user1 = new User("Keith");
$user2 = new User($_GET["name"]);

echoUserName($user1);
```

