TITLE: Handling Tainted Callable in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This PHP snippet demonstrates the use of potentially unsafe user input to invoke a function. The code accepts a string from a GET request and attempts to execute it if it is callable. This pattern can lead to security vulnerabilities, such as executing arbitrary code. The code does not handle validation or sanitization, thus allowing risky operations based on user inputs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/catchpoint/webpagetest/blob/master/vendor/vimeo/psalm/docs/running_psalm/issues/TaintedCallable.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
<?php

$name = $_GET["name"];

evalCode($name);

function evalCode(string $name) {
    if (is_callable($name)) {
        $name();
    }
}
```

