TITLE: Executing Shell Commands with Unvalidated User Input in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Example of a security vulnerability where user-supplied input from $_GET is passed directly to PHP's exec() function without validation or sanitization. This creates a critical security risk allowing arbitrary command execution.
SOURCE: https://github.com/catchpoint/webpagetest/blob/master/vendor/vimeo/psalm/docs/running_psalm/issues/TaintedShell.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

$command = $_GET["command"];

runCode($command);

function runCode(string $command) {
    exec($command);
}
```

