DESCRIPTION: Example of an insecure implementation where unvalidated user input from GET parameters is passed directly to PHP's eval() function through a wrapper function. This creates a serious security vulnerability allowing arbitrary code execution.
SOURCE: https://github.com/catchpoint/webpagetest/blob/master/vendor/vimeo/psalm/docs/running_psalm/issues/TaintedEval.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

$name = $_GET["name"];

evalCode($name);

function evalCode(string $name) {
    eval($name);
}
```

